        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 12:51PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1249 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms over
Tanglewood, or 7 miles northeast of Lexington, moving northeast at
40 mph. If these storms move into Burleson County, damaging wind
gusts and hail would be possible. These cells are being monitored
closely in case they strengthen further.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Caldwell and Chriesman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT for southeastern
Texas.</instruction>
